Title: Go for DevOps: Riding a Big Toothed Bear into Battle.

Bio:
Zack Dannar works as a DevOps for Pulsara.  In previous lives, he has provided
services to RightNow, Oracle and Zoot.  When not at work, you may find him
riding OHVs and camping around Montana.

Abstract:
Your mother or someone in life told you that "Nothing in life is free".  This
simple principle also has merit regarding your monitoring, scripts and supporting
systems on each of your hosts.  Lets consider Go as an opportunity to free some
CPU cycles, memory and deployment complexity.

